      "text": "view here today we will focus on bf",
      "start": 489.44,
      "duration": 5.759
    },
    {
      "text": "skinner's behaviorist theory of language",
      "start": 492.16,
      "duration": 5.039
    },
    {
      "text": "acquisition",
      "start": 495.199,
      "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
      "text": "and this is how he looks",
      "start": 497.199,
      "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
      "text": "anyways",
      "start": 499.919,
      "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
      "text": "skinner argued that language acquisition",
      "start": 501.039,
      "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
      "text": "and development are learned behavior",
      "start": 503.52,
      "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
      "text": "for example bathing if a child is made",
      "start": 506.479,
      "duration": 5.601
    },
    {
      "text": "how to bath and if he is made to do on",
      "start": 509.44,
      "duration": 4.079
    },
    {
      "text": "himself daily",
      "start": 512.08,
      "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
      "text": "then bathing becomes habit",
      "start": 513.519,
      "duration": 5.361
    },
    {
      "text": "similarly skinner argues that language",
      "start": 516.0,
      "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
      "text": "can be learnt like a behavior",
      "start": 518.88,
      "duration": 5.279
    },
    {
      "text": "so according to behaviorist theory",
      "start": 522.0,
      "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
      "text": "language as a behavior is a set of",
      "start": 524.159,
      "duration": 5.281
    },
    {
      "text": "habits acquired by operant conditioning",
      "start": 526.48,
      "duration": 5.52
    },
    {
      "text": "and reinforcement",
      "start": 529.44,
      "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
      "text": "means language can be acquired just like",
      "start": 532.0,
      "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
      "text": "any other behaviors like that of acting",
      "start": 534.8,
      "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
      "text": "thinking or feeling",
      "start": 537.92,
      "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
      "text": "but skinner puts condition for it to",
      "start": 540.64,
      "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
      "text": "happen he says for language to be",
      "start": 542.56,
      "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
      "text": "acquired as a behavior it has two",
      "start": 545.04,
      "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
      "text": "prerequisites",
      "start": 547.519,
      "duration": 4.481
    },
    {
      "text": "it needs to follow operant conditioning",
      "start": 549.6,
      "duration": 5.919
    },
    {
      "text": "as well as reinforcement",
      "start": 552.0,
      "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
      "text": "look in this chart how the operant",
      "start": 556.64,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "conditioning is divided into",
      "start": 558.399,
      "duration": 4.321
    },
    {
      "text": "reinforcement and punishment",
      "start": 560.08,
      "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
      "text": "we will see this in detail",
      "start": 562.72,
      "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
      "text": "first let's know what is operant",
      "start": 567.2,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "conditioning",
      "start": 569.04,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "operant conditioning is the strength of",
      "start": 570.64,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "the stimulus response bond that",
      "start": 572.48,
      "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
      "text": "determines the probability of occurrence",
      "start": 574.72,
      "duration": 5.679
    },
    {
      "text": "of a certain response or behavior",
      "start": 576.959,
      "duration": 5.681
    },
    {
      "text": "understand in this way",
      "start": 580.399,
      "duration": 5.361
    },
    {
      "text": "for example if a child is given a glass",
      "start": 582.64,
      "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
      "text": "of hot milk his parents will obviously",
      "start": 585.76,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "want him not to touch the glass",
      "start": 588.48,
      "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
      "text": "but if he accidentally touches it he",
      "start": 590.88,
      "duration": 5.6
    },
    {
      "text": "will remember the stimulus that because",
      "start": 593.68,
      "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
      "text": "it was hot",
      "start": 596.48,
      "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
      "text": "and because he touched it earlier he",
      "start": 597.92,
      "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
      "text": "will be in a position not to touch it",
      "start": 600.32,
      "duration": 5.199
    },
    {
      "text": "again so in this way a response is",
      "start": 602.399,
      "duration": 6.56
    },
    {
      "text": "developed through conditioning",
      "start": 605.519,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "now the reinforcement it comes under",
      "start": 610.32,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "operant conditioning",
      "start": 613.04,
      "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
      "text": "reinforcement is something that",
      "start": 615.44,
      "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
      "text": "increases the probability of occurrence",
      "start": 617.2,
      "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
      "text": "of a preceding behavior",
      "start": 619.44,
      "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
      "text": "this means doing a particular thing",
      "start": 621.76,
      "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
      "text": "repeatedly as we saw in the case of",
      "start": 624.32,
      "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
      "text": "bathing",
      "start": 626.8,
      "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
      "text": "the repeating tendency becomes habit and",
      "start": 628.079,
      "duration": 6.641
    },
    {
      "text": "unknowingly it becomes our behavior",
      "start": 630.56,
      "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
      "text": "now the types of reinforcement",
      "start": 634.88,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "the reinforcement is divided into",
      "start": 637.92,
      "duration": 5.039
    },
    {
      "text": "positive and negative reinforcement",
      "start": 640.0,
      "duration": 5.519
    },
    {
      "text": "the first one is the positive one",
      "start": 642.959,
      "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
      "text": "in which",
      "start": 645.519,
      "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
      "text": "there are certain benefits or reward",
      "start": 646.56,
      "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
      "text": "given following a behavior",
      "start": 648.56,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "for example giving a treat when a dog",
      "start": 651.2,
      "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
      "text": "sets",
      "start": 653.68,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "this is a kind of positive reinforcement",
      "start": 654.88,
      "duration": 5.76
    },
    {
      "text": "in which the dog is awarded with a treat",
      "start": 657.76,
      "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
      "text": "when he sits",
      "start": 660.64,
      "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
      "text": "another is negative reinforcement",
      "start": 662.56,
      "duration": 5.6
    },
    {
      "text": "in this operant conditioning the person",
      "start": 665.36,
      "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
      "text": "or animal",
      "start": 668.16,
      "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
      "text": "will either try to escape from the",
      "start": 669.519,
      "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
      "text": "harmful stimulus by following a correct",
      "start": 671.44,
      "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
      "text": "behavior",
      "start": 674.16,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "or they might avoid the harmful stimulus",
      "start": 675.36,
      "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
      "text": "completely",
      "start": 678.24,
      "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
      "text": "turning off an alarm clock by pushing",
      "start": 680.56,
      "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
      "text": "the snooze button",
      "start": 682.8,
      "duration": 4.719
    },
    {
      "text": "this can be an example of escape",
      "start": 684.399,
      "duration": 5.601
    },
    {
      "text": "the alarm was set by you because you",
      "start": 687.519,
      "duration": 5.121
    },
    {
      "text": "wanted to get up earlier but here you",
      "start": 690.0,
      "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
      "text": "are trying to escape from it by snoozing",
      "start": 692.64,
      "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
      "text": "the alarm clock",
      "start": 694.959,
      "duration": 4.961
    },
    {
      "text": "and the example of avoidance is",
      "start": 696.88,
      "duration": 7.519
    },
    {
      "text": "studying to avoid getting a bad grade",
      "start": 699.92,
      "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
      "text": "next type of operant conditioning is",
      "start": 705.279,
      "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
      "text": "punishment",
      "start": 707.36,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "which focuses on decreasing the",
      "start": 709.12,
      "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
      "text": "probability of a behavior",
      "start": 710.8,
      "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
      "text": "for example",
      "start": 713.76,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "your neighbor is playing music on",
      "start": 715.279,
      "duration": 4.961
    },
    {
      "text": "loudspeaker and it is very bad and the",
      "start": 717.2,
      "duration": 5.199
    },
    {
      "text": "old person in the locality are going",
      "start": 720.24,
      "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
      "text": "uneasy with it you will warn your",
      "start": 722.399,
      "duration": 4.801
    },
    {
      "text": "neighbor first but if he still doesn't",
      "start": 724.8,
      "duration": 4.719
    },
    {
      "text": "listen to you you will go straight away",
      "start": 727.2,
      "duration": 5.199
    },
    {
      "text": "and call the police and in this way you",
      "start": 729.519,
      "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
      "text": "can force your neighbor to stop playing",
      "start": 732.399,
      "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
      "text": "the music",
      "start": 734.399,
      "duration": 2.641
    },
    {
      "text": "like reinforcement punishment is also",
      "start": 737.92,
      "duration": 6.719
    },
    {
      "text": "subdivided into positive and negative",
      "start": 740.56,
      "duration": 6.719
    },
    {
      "text": "the positive punishment is given so that",
      "start": 744.639,
      "duration": 5.281
    },
    {
      "text": "the desired behavior is followed for",
      "start": 747.279,
      "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
      "text": "example",
      "start": 749.92,
      "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
      "text": "spanking a child for cursing",
      "start": 751.12,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "means a punishment is given to the child",
      "start": 753.6,
      "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
      "text": "in the form of slapping because he",
      "start": 756.24,
      "duration": 5.279
    },
    {
      "text": "uttered a offensive words",
      "start": 758.8,
      "duration": 4.719
    },
    {
      "text": "and this is done to see a positive",
      "start": 761.519,
      "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
      "text": "change in the behavior of child",
      "start": 763.519,
      "duration": 6.401
    },
    {
      "text": "then the negative punishment this",
      "start": 767.519,
      "duration": 5.041
    },
    {
      "text": "focuses on the removal of natural desire",
      "start": 769.92,
      "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
      "text": "to follow a behavior",
      "start": 772.56,
      "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
      "text": "for example sending a child to his room",
      "start": 774.8,
      "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
      "text": "for cursing",
      "start": 777.44,
      "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
      "text": "now if the child is given punishment",
      "start": 779.36,
      "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
      "text": "again and again for the same cause and",
      "start": 781.6,
      "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
      "text": "after a certain period of time he will",
      "start": 784.32,
      "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
      "text": "understand that",
      "start": 786.24,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "by doing so and so he is getting",
      "start": 787.839,
      "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
      "text": "punishment so therefore he will try to",
      "start": 789.68,
      "duration": 6.399
    },
    {
      "text": "avoid this in the future",
      "start": 792.639,
      "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
      "text": "and here comes the famous skinner box",
      "start": 797.36,
      "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
      "text": "also known as operant conditioning",
      "start": 799.76,
      "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
      "text": "chamber",
      "start": 801.6,
      "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
      "text": "the idea behind this experiment is to",
      "start": 803.44,
      "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
      "text": "prove whatever is laid down by skinner",
      "start": 805.76,
      "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
      "text": "in the behaviorist theory",
      "start": 807.92,
      "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
      "text": "now as you can see on your screen",
      "start": 811.04,
      "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
      "text": "that the rat that was placed in the box",
      "start": 813.6,
      "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
      "text": "did not know what the lever was for at",
      "start": 815.839,
      "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
      "text": "the first",
      "start": 818.24,
      "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
      "text": "the rat pressed the lever food",
      "start": 819.6,
      "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
      "text": "eventually came out of it",
      "start": 821.6,
      "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
      "text": "and the rat when he gets hungry",
      "start": 823.519,
      "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
      "text": "continues to press the lever and get",
      "start": 825.6,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "satisfied with the food",
      "start": 827.839,
      "duration": 5.601
    },
    {
      "text": "he does this because this is the operand",
      "start": 830.72,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "behavior",
      "start": 833.44,
      "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
      "text": "because this is an action that results",
      "start": 834.8,
      "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
      "text": "with a consequence",
      "start": 837.279,
      "duration": 4.881
    },
    {
      "text": "the foot acts as a reinforcer because it",
      "start": 839.12,
      "duration": 6.8
    },
    {
      "text": "causes the operand behavior to increase",
      "start": 842.16,
      "duration": 6.32
    },
    {
      "text": "however the operand behavior may come to",
      "start": 845.92,
      "duration": 5.359
    },
    {
      "text": "the point of end when the rat continues",
      "start": 848.48,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "to press the lever and yet food does not",
      "start": 851.279,
      "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
      "text": "come out",
      "start": 853.6,
      "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
      "text": "the rat will then automatically cease on",
      "start": 854.72,
      "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
      "text": "pressing the lever",
      "start": 857.12,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "thus stopping an operand behavior",
      "start": 858.639,
      "duration": 5.361
    },
    {
      "text": "and this is all that is there in the",
      "start": 862.24,
      "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
      "text": "behaviors theory",
      "start": 864.0,
      "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
      "text": "now cognitive theory of language",
      "start": 868.8,
      "duration": 5.839
    },
    {
      "text": "acquisition by norm chomsky",
      "start": 870.88,
      "duration": 6.399
    },
    {
      "text": "cognitive theory of language acquisition",
      "start": 874.639,
      "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
      "text": "was put forward by norm chomsky in the",
      "start": 877.279,
      "duration": 4.881
    },
    {
      "text": "year 1960s",
      "start": 879.839,
      "duration": 4.961
    },
    {
      "text": "the theory rejects or somehow neglects",
      "start": 882.16,
      "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
      "text": "social or behavioral aspect of language",
      "start": 884.8,
      "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
      "text": "acquisition and focuses on the human",
      "start": 887.44,
      "duration": 5.519
    },
    {
      "text": "mind and natural capacity of human mind",
      "start": 890.16,
      "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
      "text": "to learn and acquire a language",
      "start": 892.959,
      "duration": 5.761
    },
    {
      "text": "it follows the mentalist approach",
      "start": 896.0,
      "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
      "text": "based upon cognition or cognitive",
      "start": 898.72,
      "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
      "text": "learning relating to the mental action",
      "start": 901.04,
      "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
      "text": "or process of acquiring knowledge",
      "start": 903.6,
      "duration": 4.239
    },
    {
      "text": "through the means related to mind and",
      "start": 905.76,
      "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
      "text": "thought process",
      "start": 907.839,
      "duration": 4.721
    },
    {
      "text": "it argues language acquisition to be a",
      "start": 909.76,
      "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
      "text": "inner structure or function of human",
      "start": 912.56,
      "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
      "text": "brain",
      "start": 914.72,
      "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
      "text": "means this is the inborn ability of",
      "start": 915.839,
      "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
      "text": "human brain to naturally acquire",
      "start": 918.24,
      "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
      "text": "language",
      "start": 920.24,
      "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
      "text": "for example when children are exposed to",
      "start": 921.839,
      "duration": 6.24
    },
    {
      "text": "speech words sounds phrases or",
      "start": 924.72,
      "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
      "text": "grammatical rules",
      "start": 928.079,
      "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
      "text": "then this structuring of language",
      "start": 929.68,
      "duration": 6.079
    },
    {
      "text": "automatically begins to operate",
      "start": 931.92,
      "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
      "text": "then norm chomsky discusses the concept",
      "start": 936.16,
      "duration": 6.08
    },
    {
      "text": "of universal grammar in detail",
      "start": 939.12,
      "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
      "text": "according to it there are set of init",
      "start": 942.24,
      "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
      "text": "principles and adjustable parameters",
      "start": 944.56,
      "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
      "text": "that are common to all human languages",
      "start": 947.199,
      "duration": 6.241
    },
    {
      "text": "means human languages are constructed on",
      "start": 950.48,
      "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
      "text": "the same abstract template",
      "start": 953.44,
      "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
      "text": "and this explains why all normal",
      "start": 955.6,
      "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
      "text": "speakers acquire the native language",
      "start": 957.92,
      "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
      "text": "quickly",
      "start": 959.92,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "for example there are grammatical",
      "start": 961.839,
      "duration": 5.201
    },
    {
      "text": "concepts present in almost all languages",
      "start": 964.0,
      "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
      "text": "with slight difference",
      "start": 967.04,
      "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
      "text": "this grammatical rules guide us to",
      "start": 968.959,
      "duration": 5.041
    },
    {
      "text": "acquire language in a proper direction",
      "start": 971.12,
      "duration": 5.839
    },
    {
      "text": "so the presence of universal grammar",
      "start": 974.0,
      "duration": 4.959
